#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:1
msgid "Comments and Documentation"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:3
msgid ""
"API documentation describes API meaning and usage and is rendered by "
"rustdoc. Public APIs should be documented, including crates, modules, "
"structs, traits, functions, and macros. The `#![warn(missing_docs)]` lint "
"helps enforce this baseline."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:9
msgid ""
"Asterinas follows Rust community documentation conventions. Two primary "
"references are:"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:11
msgid ""
"The rustdoc book: [How to write documentation](https://doc.rust-lang.org/"
"rustdoc/how-to-write-documentation.html)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:13
msgid ""
"The Rust RFC book: [API Documentation Conventions](https://rust-lang.github."
"io/rfcs/1574-more-api-documentation-conventions.html#appendix-a-full-"
"conventions-text)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:16
msgid "Follow RFC 1574 summary line conventions (`rfc1574-summary`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:18
msgid ""
"The first line of a doc comment should be concise and one sentence. Its "
"grammatical form depends on what the item is:"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:21
msgid ""
"**Functions and methods** — third-person singular present indicative verb "
"(\"Returns\", \"Creates\", \"Acquires\"), describing the action performed."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:23
msgid ""
"**Types (structs, enums, traits, type aliases), modules, and fields** — a "
"noun phrase naming the thing, not describing an action. This matches the "
"Rust standard library convention (e.g., `Vec` is \"A contiguous growable "
"array type\")."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:29
msgid "/// Returns the mapping's start address.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:33
msgid ""
"/// A policy for how [`FsPath::from_fd_at`] treats an empty `path_str`.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:35
#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:38
msgid "/* ... */"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:36
msgid "/// A guard that releases a [`SpinLock`] when dropped.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:41
msgid "End sentence comments with punctuation (`comment-punctuation`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:43
msgid ""
"If a comment line is a full sentence, end it with proper punctuation. This "
"improves readability in dense code and avoids fragmented prose."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:49
msgid ""
"// Good — complete sentence with punctuation.\n"
"// SAFETY: The pointer is derived from a live allocation.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:51
msgid ""
"// Bad — complete sentence without punctuation\n"
"// SAFETY: The pointer is derived from a live allocation\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:56
msgid "Wrap identifiers in backticks (`backtick-identifiers`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:58
msgid ""
"Type names, method names, and code identifiers in doc comments should be "
"wrapped in backticks for rustdoc rendering. When referring to types, prefer "
"rustdoc links (`[TypeName]`) where possible."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:65
msgid ""
"/// Acquires the [`SpinLock`] and returns a guard\n"
"/// that releases the lock on [`Drop`].\n"
"///\n"
"/// Callers must not call `acquire` while holding\n"
"/// a [`RwMutex`] to avoid deadlock.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:73
msgid ""
"Do not disclose implementation details in doc comments (`no-impl-in-docs`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:75
msgid ""
"Doc comments should describe _what_ the API does and _how to use it_, not "
"_how it is implemented internally_."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:80
msgid ""
"// Good — behavior-oriented\n"
"/// Returns the number of active connections.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:82
msgid ""
"// Bad — leaks implementation details\n"
"/// Returns the length of the internal `HashMap`\n"
"/// that tracks connections by socket address.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:88
msgid "Add module-level documentation for major components (`module-docs`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:90
msgid ""
"A module file that serves as an important kernel component (e.g., subsystem "
"entry point, major data structure, driver) should begin with a `//!` comment "
"explaining:"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:94
msgid "What the module does"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:95
msgid "The key types it exposes"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:96
msgid "How it relates to neighboring modules"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:99
msgid ""
"//! Virtual memory area (VMA) management.\n"
"//!\n"
"//! This module defines [`VmMapping`] and associated types,\n"
"//! which represent contiguous regions of a process's virtual address "
"space.\n"
"//! VMAs are managed by the [`Vmar`] tree in the parent module.\n"
msgstr ""
